event.content:
South Orange County Cars & Coffee

The South OC Cars And Coffee events were started sometime after the legendary Irvine events were shut down.  And this one definitely filled an unmet need.

Because it quickly out-grew the original location and now hosts between 500 and 600 cars weekly.  And if your vehicle has wheels and a motor, it sounds like it’s welcome here.

Common sights include supers, hypers, muscle, classics, rods, trucks, and motorcycles.  But, of course, you don’t have to bring a car to put on display.  Everyone is welcome to attend and enjoy the camaraderie of fellow car guys and gals.

And speaking of that… in case you haven’t connected the dots yet.  Here’s the perfect opportunity to get your non-car-loving partner to a cool show.  Because the show ends exactly one-hour after the outlet stores open.

South Orange County Cars & Coffee

Dates: Every Saturday
Location: Outlets At San Clemente
Starts: 9 AM (no entry before 8:30 AM – strictly)
Ends: 11 AM
Admission: Free
Vehicle Registration: Free

*Please note: iDriveSoCal does not host this event.  So if you’d like to learn more about the event please contact organizers HERE.  And that includes more specific details about attending, displaying your vehicle, and becoming a vendor or sponsor.

For more of the best Southern California automotive events click HERE.

First-timer?  Review our Cars And Coffee Ultimate Guide before you go to feel like a pro!

Ever wonder how cars and coffee events got started?  Check out this podcast on The History Of Cars And Coffee!

Have an event that you think we should post?  Contact us HERE.
